# MindFocus — Environment Variables
# Copy to .env.local and fill in your values.
# Never commit .env.local to source control (it is in .gitignore).
#
# All VITE_* variables are bundled into the client-side JS and are
# therefore publicly visible. Only keys safe for public exposure go here.
# See docs/bolts/adr/0014-pwa-deploy.md and adr/0015-edge-function-proxy.md.

# ── Supabase ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Project URL (Settings → API → Project URL)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co

# Anon / public key — safe to expose, protected by Row Level Security (RLS)
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# ── Anthropic Claude API — SERVER-SIDE ONLY (Supabase Secret) ─────────────────
# The Anthropic API key is stored in Supabase Secrets, NOT here.
# It never reaches the browser. All AI calls proxy through the Edge Function.
#
# Set once, run in your terminal (requires Supabase CLI):
#   supabase secrets set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-...
#
# Or via Supabase Dashboard → Settings → Edge Functions → Secrets.
# Docs: https://supabase.com/docs/guides/functions/secrets
#
# Variable name:  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY  (no VITE_ prefix — server-side only)
# Edge Function:  supabase/functions/ai-proxy/index.ts
